   <title>TAN-A-div elements and attributes summarized</title>
   <para>
      <emphasis>Elements</emphasis>: TAN-A-div anchor-div-ref div-ref div-type-ref equate-div-types equate-works realign split-leaf-div-at</para>
   <para>
      <emphasis>Attributes</emphasis>: alignments distribute exclusive seg strength</para>
   <section xml:id="tan-element-anchor-div-ref">
      <title>
         <code>&lt;anchor-div-ref&gt;</code>
      </title>
      <para>Element: <code>anchor-div-ref</code>:
            <emphasis>References a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> to which other <code>&lt;div-ref&gt;</code>s should be realigned</emphasis>
      </para>
      <para>Definition: <code>(@src, @ref, (@ed-who, @ed-when)?, @seg?)</code>
      </para>
      <para>Used by: <code>realign<xref linkend="tan-element-realign"/>
         </code>
      </para>
   </section>
   <section xml:id="tan-element-div-ref">
      <title>
         <code>&lt;div-ref&gt;</code>
      </title>
      <para>Element: <code>div-ref</code>:
            <emphasis>References a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>
         </emphasis>
      </para>
      <para>Definition: <code>(@src, @ref, (@ed-who, @ed-when)?, @seg?)</code>
      </para>
      <para>Used by: <code>realign<xref linkend="tan-element-realign"/>
         </code>
         <code>align<xref linkend="tan-element-align"/>
         </code>
      </para>
   </section>
   <section xml:id="tan-element-div-type-ref">
      <title>
         <code>&lt;div-type-ref&gt;</code>
      </title>
      <para>Element: <code>div-type-ref</code>:
            <emphasis>References a <code>&lt;div-type&gt;</code> in a class 1 source</emphasis>
      </para>
      <para>Definition: <code>(@ed-who, @ed-when)?, @src, @div-type-ref</code>
      </para>
      <para>Used by: <code>equate-div-types<xref linkend="tan-element-equate-div-types"/>
         </code>
      </para>
   </section>
   <section xml:id="tan-element-equate-div-types">
      <title>
         <code>&lt;equate-div-types&gt;</code>
      </title>
      <para>Element: <code>equate-div-types</code>:
            <emphasis>Declares an ad hoc equivalence of div types for class 1 sources that have no shared <code>&lt;IRI&gt;</code>s
under a particular <code>&lt;div-type&gt;</code> 
         </emphasis>
      </para>
      <para>Definition: <code>(@ed-who, @ed-when)?, (@include, &lt;div-type-ref&gt; , &lt;div-type-ref&gt;)</code>
      </para>
      <para>Used by: <code>body<xref linkend="tan-element-body"/>
         </code>
      </para>
   </section>
   <section xml:id="tan-element-equate-works">
      <title>
         <code>&lt;equate-works&gt;</code>
      </title>
      <para>Element: <code>equate-works</code>:
            <emphasis>Declares an ad hoc equivalence of works for class 1 sources that have no shared <code>&lt;IRI&gt;</code>s 
under <code>&lt;work&gt;</code>
         </emphasis>
      </para>
      <para>Definition: <code>(@ed-who, @ed-when)?, (@include, | @src)</code>
      </para>
      <para>Used by: <code>body<xref linkend="tan-element-body"/>
         </code>
      </para>
   </section>
   <section xml:id="tan-element-realign">
      <title>
         <code>&lt;realign&gt;</code>
      </title>
      <para>Element: <code>realign</code>:
            <emphasis>Reassigns the default alignment of <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>s in a class 1 source 
to zero or more locations in other versions of the same work</emphasis>
      </para>
      <para>Definition: <code>(@ed-who, @ed-when)?, (@include, &lt;comment&gt; &lt;anchor-div-ref&gt;?, &lt;div-ref&gt;)</code>
      </para>
      <para>Used by: <code>body<xref linkend="tan-element-body"/>
         </code>
      </para>
   </section>
   <section xml:id="tan-element-split-leaf-div-at">
      <title>
         <code>&lt;split-leaf-div-at&gt;</code>
      </title>
      <para>Element: <code>split-leaf-div-at</code>:
            <emphasis>Creates ad hoc splits in leaf <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>s, to create alignments more refined 
than what a class 1 source offers; useful for <code>&lt;realign&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;align&gt;</code> actions that
require dealing with textual units smaller than leaf <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>s.</emphasis>
      </para>
      <para>Definition: <code>(@ed-who, @ed-when)?, (@include, &lt;comment&gt; &lt;tok&gt;)</code>
      </para>
      <para>Used by: <code>body<xref linkend="tan-element-body"/>
         </code>
      </para>
   </section>
